gomodel:SYNGO_1316  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors generate two independent shRNAs against the rat sequence of JAK2 in order to investigate the role of the protein in NMDA-LTD. Transfected hippocampal organotypic slices were used to test this. While basal synaptic transmission was unaffected in transfected slices, NMDA-LTD was absent in those neurons expressing the shRNAs against JAK2 while neurons expressing the control shRNA did express LTD as expected.. Experimental description: Experiments were performed in rat hippocampal slices and the shRNAs used agains JAK2 were generated against the rat sequence. Literal \"the sequences of the 29-mer shRNAs against rat JAK2 were GCCATCAGCAAACTAAAGAAGGCAGGAAA for the shRNA-1 and CAGCCTGTTTACTCCAGATTATGAACTGC for the shRNA-2.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1316" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

